nnconfigMgmtMib.name: nnconfigMgmtMib

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

nnconfigMgmtMib.contactinfo: Nortel Networks 8200 Dixie Road Brampton, Ontario L6T 5P6 Canada 1-800-4Nortel www.nortelnetworks.com
nnconfigMgmtMib.description: Configuration management MIB. This MIB represents a model of configuration data that exists in various locations: current In use by the running system. local Saved locally in NVRAM or flash. remote Saved to some server on the network. The purpose of this MIB is to track changes and saves of the current configuration.

nncfgNetOperTable.name: nncfgNetOperTable
nncfgNetOperTable.description: A table of configuration from network operation entries. Each entry represents a separate operation to configure the system from a file located on a server on the network. The management station should create an entry with a random number as an index to perform the operation. The management station should then retrieve the entry with the same random number as an index and examine the value of the cfgNetOperStatus variable to get the status of the operation.

nncfgNetOperEntry.name: nncfgNetOperEntry
nncfgNetOperEntry.description: Entry to initiate an operation. Each entry consists of a command and required parameters. Once the operation completes, the management station should retrieve the value of the status object and delete the entry from the table.

nncfgNetOperRandomNumber.name: nncfgNetOperRandomNumber
nncfgNetOperRandomNumber.description: Object specifying a unique entry in the table. A management station wishing to initiate a configuration operation should use a pseudo-random value for this object when creating a cfgNetOperEntry.

nncfgNetOperCommand.name: nncfgNetOperCommand
nncfgNetOperCommand.description: The commands to be executed configure from the network or save the configuration to the network. Command Remarks. config Configure from network. save Save configuration to network.

nncfgNetOperAddress.name: nncfgNetOperAddress
nncfgNetOperAddress.description: The Internet address of the server.

nncfgNetOperFileName.name: nncfgNetOperFileName
nncfgNetOperFileName.description: The destination or source file name on the network server.

nncfgNetOperStatus.name: nncfgNetOperStatus
nncfgNetOperStatus.description: Represents the status of the operation. If the operation has not started or an operation is not being performed, then the value of this object would be idle(0).

CfgMedium.name: CfgMedium
CfgMedium.description: The source or destination of a configuration change, save, or copy. commandSource The source of the command. current Live operational data from RAM. flash Local flash. network Network host.

nncfgCurrentLastChanged.name: nncfgCurrentLastChanged
nncfgCurrentLastChanged.description: The last time the current configuration was changed.

nncfgCurrentLastSaved.name: nncfgCurrentLastSaved
nncfgCurrentLastSaved.description: The last time the current configuration was saved.

nncfgMaxEvents.name: nncfgMaxEvents
nncfgMaxEvents.description: The maximum number of entries that can be held in the cfgEventTable. The system stores the 20 most recent history events in a circular style. These events are also saved to flash. Up to the last 10 entries can be saved if space is available in flash.

nncfgEventTable.name: nncfgEventTable
nncfgEventTable.description: A table of configuration history events.

nncfgEventEntry.name: nncfgEventEntry
nncfgEventEntry.description: Entry holding information about a configuration event.

nncfgEventIndex.name: nncfgEventIndex
nncfgEventIndex.description: Index in the history event table.

nncfgEventTime.name: nncfgEventTime
nncfgEventTime.description: The time when the configuration occurred.

nncfgEventConfigProtocol.name: nncfgEventConfigProtocol
nncfgEventConfigProtocol.description: The source of the command that resulted in the event.

nncfgEventConfigSrc.name: nncfgEventConfigSrc
nncfgEventConfigSrc.description: The configuration data source for the event.

nncfgEventConfigDst.name: nncfgEventConfigDst
nncfgEventConfigDst.description: The configuration data destination for the event.

nncfgEventLoginType.name: nncfgEventLoginType
nncfgEventLoginType.description: Configuration via telnet or rlogin, etc.

nncfgEventTerminalUser.name: nncfgEventTerminalUser
nncfgEventTerminalUser.description: This object represents the logged in user name if configuration is via the CLI. It represents the community name if configuration is via SNMP. Otherwise, the object string length is zero if not available or not applicable.

nncfgEventConfigSrcAddress.name: nncfgEventConfigSrcAddress
nncfgEventConfigSrcAddress.description: The Internet address of the connected system. The value is 0.0.0.0 if not available or not applicable.

nncfgEventFileName.name: nncfgEventFileName
nncfgEventFileName.description: If the system is set for configuration via a network, then this object represents the file name on some server.

nncfgEnableChangeNotification.name: nncfgEnableChangeNotification
nncfgEnableChangeNotification.description: Indicates whether the system produces the cfgChangeNotification. The default is yes.

nncfgEnableSaveNotification.name: nncfgEnableSaveNotification
nncfgEnableSaveNotification.description: Indicates whether the system produces the cfgSaveNotification. The default is yes.

nncfgEventChangeNotification.name: nncfgEventChangeNotification
nncfgEventChangeNotification.description: Send the configuration change event via either trap or info request PDU

nncfgEventSaveNotification.name: nncfgEventSaveNotification
nncfgEventSaveNotification.description: Send the configuration save event via either trap or info request PDU
